TCS NQT Statement and Conclusion Quiz-2

Question 1

P + Q = P is greater than Q.
P - Q = P is either greater than or equal to Q.
P * Q = P is smaller than Q.         P / Q = P is either smaller than or equal to Q.
P % Q = P is equal to Q.
Statement: S+ T, U * S, T * S, S - M, Q - R.
Conclusions
1. T+U
2. M/T

If conclusion 1 is true

If conclusion 2 is true

If both conclusion 1 and 2 are true

If either conclusion 1 or 2 are true

If neither conclusion 1 nor 2 is true

  • PrepInsta Explanation
  • User Explanation
Once you attempt the question then PrepInsta explanation will be displayed.

S>T, U<S, T<S, S>=M, Q>=R
Conclusion 1: T>U and U<S, which implies UT, that is U can either be < T or = T or >T
Conclusion 2: M<=T and S>=M, which implies T>=M<=S. Therefore, nothing can be concluded

Question 2

A # B = A is neither greater than nor equal B.
A ! B = A is neither equal nor smaller than B.
A % B = A is neither smaller nor greater than B.
A $ B = A is not smaller than B.
A @ B = A is not greater than B.
Statement: P @ Q, Q ! R, S $ R.
Conclusions
1. R # P
2. S ! Q

If conclusion 1 is true

If conclusion 2 is true

If both conclusion 1 and 2 are true

If either conclusion 1 or 2 are true

If neither conclusion 1 nor 2 is true

  • PrepInsta Explanation
  • User Explanation
Once you attempt the question then PrepInsta explanation will be displayed.

P<=Q, Q>R, S>=R
P<=Q>R<=S
Conclusion 1: R

Q
Therefore, no conclusion can be derived.

Question 3

. A B = A is smaller than B.
A B = A is greater than B.
A B = A is equal to B.
A B = A is greater than equal to B.
A B = A is smaller than or equal to B.
Statement: H V, V M, K M
Conclusions
1. K V
2. M H
3. H K

If conclusion 1 is true

If all are true

If conclusion 2 is true

If both conclusion 1 or 2 are true

If none is true

  • PrepInsta Explanation
  • User Explanation
Once you attempt the question then PrepInsta explanation will be displayed.

Both conclusion one and two are true.

Explanation-

From the given statements we derive a conclusion that H>=V, K>V  but there is no relation given between H and K , so we cannot conclude that H>K

Question 4

. M + N = A is smaller than B.
M * N = A is greater than or equal to B.
M & N = A is smaller than or equal to B.
M $ N = A is greater than B.
M # N = A is equal to B.
Statement: T + Q, S * M, Q * R, U + S, S + T
Conclusions
1. Q $ S
2. U + T

If conclusion 1 is true

If conclusion 2 is true

If both conclusion 1 and 2 are true

If either conclusion 1 or 2 are true

If neither conclusion 1 nor 2 is true

  • PrepInsta Explanation
  • User Explanation
Once you attempt the question then PrepInsta explanation will be displayed.

T<Q, S>=M, Q>=R, U<S, S<T
U<S<T=R, S>=M
Conclusion 1: Q>S
Conclusion 2: U<T
Therefore, conclusion 1 and 2 are true.

Question 5

U || V = U is neither greater nor smaller than V.
U | V = U is neither smaller nor equal V.
U : V = U is smaller than or equal to V.
U ~ V = U is greater than or equal V.
U ? V = U is neither greater nor equal to V.
Statement: D ~ G, G || F, F | E,
Conclusions
1. D || F
2. E | G

If conclusion 1 is true

If conclusion 2 is true

If both conclusion 1 and 2 are true

If either conclusion 1 or 2 are true

If neither conclusion 1 nor 2 is true

  • PrepInsta Explanation
  • User Explanation
Once you attempt the question then PrepInsta explanation will be displayed.

D>=G, = F, F>E
D>=G=F>E
Conclusion 1: D=F
Conclusion 2: E>G
Therefore, only 1 is true.

Question 6

P^Q = P greater than Q.

P@Q = P smaller than or equal to Q.

P!Q = P is equal to Q.

P*Q = P is greater than equal to Q.

P&Q = P is smaller than Q.

Statement: A*B, C!A, C*E

Conclusions 1. C*B 2. B@E

If conclusion 1 is true

If conclusion 2 is true

If both conclusion 1 and 2 are true

If either conclusion 1 or 2 are true

If neither conclusion 1 nor 2 is true

  • PrepInsta Explanation
  • User Explanation
Once you attempt the question then PrepInsta explanation will be displayed.

A>=B, C=B, C>E
A>=B=C>E
Conclusion 1: C>=B
Conclusion 2: B<=E
Therefore, only 1 is true.

Question 7

+ denotes less than.

- denotes greater than.

* denotes not less than.

/ denotes not greater than.

% denotes equal to.

$ denotes not equal to

Statement: P%Q, R/S, Q*R

Conclusions 1. P%S 2. Q-R

If conclusion 1 is true

If conclusion 2 is true

If both conclusion 1 and 2 are true

If either conclusion 1 or 2 are true

If neither conclusion 1 nor 2 is true

  • PrepInsta Explanation
  • User Explanation
Once you attempt the question then PrepInsta explanation will be displayed.

P=Q, R<=S, Q>=R
P=Q>=R<=S Conclusion 1: P=S Conclusion 2: Q>R
Therefore, only 2 is true.

Question 8

The questions contain some statements followed by some conclusions. Decide which of the given conclusion logically follow from the given statements, disregarding commonly known facts. Statements: P: All the players have the ability to win Q: All the players have to eat well. Conclusion: I. All those who eat well are good players. II. All players who want to win have to eat well. Hint:-

 

Only conclusion I follow

Only conclusion II follows

Neither I or II follows

Both I and II follows

  • PrepInsta Explanation
  • User Explanation
Once you attempt the question then PrepInsta explanation will be displayed.

Clearly from the diagram the players need to eat well to win.
